  "root_text": {
    "dhp256:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp256:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp256:0.3": "Dhammaṭṭhavagga ",
    "dhp256:0.4": "Vinicchayamahāmattavatthu ",
    "dhp256:1": "Na tena hoti dhammaṭṭho, ",
    "dhp256:2": "yenatthaṁ sāhasā naye; ",
    "dhp256:3": "Yo ca atthaṁ anatthañca, ",
    "dhp256:4": "ubho niccheyya paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp257:1": "Asāhasena dhammena, ",
    "dhp257:2": "samena nayatī pare; ",
    "dhp257:3": "Dhammassa gutto medhāvī, ",
    "dhp257:4": "“dhammaṭṭho”ti pavuccati. ",
    "dhp258:0": "Chabbaggiyavatthu ",
    "dhp258:1": "Na tena paṇḍito hoti, ",
    "dhp258:2": "yāvatā bahu bhāsati; ",
    "dhp258:3": "Khemī averī abhayo, ",
    "dhp258:4": "“paṇḍito”ti pavuccati. ",
    "dhp259:0": "Ekudānakhīṇāsavavatthu ",
    "dhp259:1": "Na tāvatā dhammadharo, ",
    "dhp259:2": "yāvatā bahu bhāsati; ",
    "dhp259:3": "Yo ca appampi sutvāna, ",
    "dhp259:4": "dhammaṁ kāyena passati; ",
    "dhp259:5": "Sa ve dhammadharo hoti, ",
    "dhp259:6": "yo dhammaṁ nappamajjati. ",
    "dhp260:0": "Lakuṇḍakabhaddiyattheravatthu ",
    "dhp260:1": "Na tena thero so hoti, ",
    "dhp260:2": "yenassa palitaṁ siro; ",
    "dhp260:3": "Paripakko vayo tassa, ",
    "dhp260:4": "“moghajiṇṇo”ti vuccati. ",
    "dhp261:1": "Yamhi saccañca dhammo ca, ",
    "dhp261:2": "ahiṁsā saṁyamo damo; ",
    "dhp261:3": "Sa ve vantamalo dhīro, ",
    "dhp261:4": "“thero” iti pavuccati. ",
    "dhp262:0": "Sambahulabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp262:1": "Na vākkaraṇamattena, ",
    "dhp262:2": "vaṇṇapokkharatāya vā; ",
    "dhp262:3": "Sādhurūpo naro hoti, ",
    "dhp262:4": "issukī maccharī saṭho. ",
    "dhp263:1": "Yassa cetaṁ samucchinnaṁ, ",
    "dhp263:2": "mūlaghaccaṁ samūhataṁ; ",
    "dhp263:3": "Sa vantadoso medhāvī, ",
    "dhp263:4": "“sādhurūpo”ti vuccati. ",
    "dhp264:0": "Hatthakavatthu ",
    "dhp264:1": "Na muṇḍakena samaṇo, ",
    "dhp264:2": "abbato alikaṁ bhaṇaṁ; ",
    "dhp264:3": "Icchālobhasamāpanno, ",
    "dhp264:4": "samaṇo kiṁ bhavissati. ",
    "dhp265:1": "Yo ca sameti pāpāni, ",
    "dhp265:2": "aṇuṁthūlāni sabbaso; ",
    "dhp265:3": "Samitattā hi pāpānaṁ, ",
    "dhp265:4": "“samaṇo”ti pavuccati. ",
    "dhp266:0": "Aññatarabrāhmaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp266:1": "Na tena bhikkhu so hoti, ",
    "dhp266:2": "yāvatā bhikkhate pare; ",
    "dhp266:3": "Vissaṁ dhammaṁ samādāya, ",
    "dhp266:4": "bhikkhu hoti na tāvatā. ",
    "dhp267:1": "Yodha puññañca pāpañca, ",
    "dhp267:2": "bāhetvā brahmacariyavā; ",
    "dhp267:3": "Saṅkhāya loke carati, ",
    "dhp267:4": "sa ve “bhikkhū”ti vuccati. ",
    "dhp268:0": "Titthiyavatthu ",
    "dhp268:1": "Na monena munī hoti, ",
    "dhp268:2": "mūḷharūpo aviddasu; ",
    "dhp268:3": "Yo ca tulaṁva paggayha, ",
    "dhp268:4": "varamādāya paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp269:1": "Pāpāni parivajjeti, ",
    "dhp269:2": "sa munī tena so muni; ",
    "dhp269:3": "Yo munāti ubho loke, ",
    "dhp269:4": "“muni” tena pavuccati. ",
    "dhp270:0": "Bālisikavatthu ",
    "dhp270:1": "Na tena ariyo hoti, ",
    "dhp270:2": "yena pāṇāni hiṁsati; ",
    "dhp270:3": "Ahiṁsā sabbapāṇānaṁ, ",
    "dhp270:4": "“ariyo”ti pavuccati. ",
    "dhp271:0": "Sambahulasīlādisampannabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp271:1": "Na sīlabbatamattena, ",
    "dhp271:2": "bāhusaccena vā pana; ",
    "dhp271:3": "Atha vā samādhilābhena, ",
    "dhp271:4": "vivittasayanena vā. ",
    "dhp272:1": "Phusāmi nekkhammasukhaṁ, ",
    "dhp272:2": "aputhujjanasevitaṁ; ",
    "dhp272:3": "Bhikkhu vissāsamāpādi, ",
    "dhp272:4": "appatto āsavakkhayaṁ. ",
    "dhp272:5": "Dhammaṭṭhavaggo ekūnavīsatimo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp256:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp256:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 256–272 ",
    "dhp256:0.3": "19. The Just ",
    "dhp256:0.4": "",
    "dhp256:1": "You don’t become just ",
    "dhp256:2": "by passing hasty judgment. ",
    "dhp256:3": "An astute person evaluates both ",
    "dhp256:4": "what is pertinent and what is irrelevant. ",
    "dhp257:1": "A wise one judges others without haste, ",
    "dhp257:2": "justly and impartially; ",
    "dhp257:3": "that guardian of the law ",
    "dhp257:4": "is said to be just. ",
    "dhp258:0": "",
    "dhp258:1": "You’re not an astute scholar ",
    "dhp258:2": "just because you speak a lot. ",
    "dhp258:3": "One who is secure, free of enmity and fear, ",
    "dhp258:4": "is said to be astute. ",
    "dhp259:0": "",
    "dhp259:1": "You’re not one who has memorized the teaching ",
    "dhp259:2": "just because you recite a lot. ",
    "dhp259:3": "Someone who directly sees the teaching ",
    "dhp259:4": "after hearing only a little ",
    "dhp259:5": "is truly one who has memorized the teaching, ",
    "dhp259:6": "for they can never forget it. ",
    "dhp260:0": "",
    "dhp260:1": "You don’t become a senior ",
    "dhp260:2": "by getting some grey hairs; ",
    "dhp260:3": "for one ripe only in age, ",
    "dhp260:4": "is said to have aged in vain. ",
    "dhp261:1": "One who is truthful and principled, ",
    "dhp261:2": "harmless, restrained, and self-controlled, ",
    "dhp261:3": "attentive, purged of stains, ",
    "dhp261:4": "is said to be a senior. ",
    "dhp262:0": "",
    "dhp262:1": "Not by mere enunciation, ",
    "dhp262:2": "or a beautiful complexion ",
    "dhp262:3": "does a person become holy, ",
    "dhp262:4": "if they’re jealous, stingy, and devious. ",
    "dhp263:1": "But if they’ve cut that out, ",
    "dhp263:2": "dug it up at the root, eradicated it, ",
    "dhp263:3": "that wise one, purged of vice, ",
    "dhp263:4": "is said to be holy. ",
    "dhp264:0": "",
    "dhp264:1": "A liar and breaker of vows is no ascetic ",
    "dhp264:2": "just because they shave their head. ",
    "dhp264:3": "How on earth can one be an ascetic ",
    "dhp264:4": "who’s full of desire and greed? ",
    "dhp265:1": "One who stops all wicked deeds, ",
    "dhp265:2": "great and small, ",
    "dhp265:3": "because of stopping wicked deeds ",
    "dhp265:4": "is said to be an ascetic. ",
    "dhp266:0": "",
    "dhp266:1": "You don’t become a mendicant ",
    "dhp266:2": "just by begging from others. ",
    "dhp266:3": "One who has undertaken domestic duties ",
    "dhp266:4": "has not yet become a mendicant. ",
    "dhp267:1": "But one living a spiritual life, ",
    "dhp267:2": "who has banished both merit and evil, ",
    "dhp267:3": "who wanders having appraised the world, ",
    "dhp267:4": "is said to be a mendicant. ",
    "dhp268:0": "",
    "dhp268:1": "You don’t become a sage by being sagelike, ",
    "dhp268:2": "while still confused and ignorant. ",
    "dhp268:3": "The astute one who holds the scales, ",
    "dhp268:4": "taking only the best, ",
    "dhp269:1": "and shunning the bad—",
    "dhp269:2": "that is a sage, <j>and that is how one becomes a sage. ",
    "dhp269:3": "One who sagely weighs both in the world, ",
    "dhp269:4": "is thereby said to be a sage. ",
    "dhp270:0": "",
    "dhp270:1": "You don’t become a noble one ",
    "dhp270:2": "by harming living beings. ",
    "dhp270:3": "One harmless towards all living beings ",
    "dhp270:4": "is said to be a noble one. ",
    "dhp271:0": "",
    "dhp271:1": "Not by precepts and observances, ",
    "dhp271:2": "nor by much learning, ",
    "dhp271:3": "nor by meditative immersion, ",
    "dhp271:4": "nor by living in seclusion, ",
    "dhp272:1": "do I experience the bliss of renunciation ",
    "dhp272:2": "not frequented by ordinary people. ",
    "dhp272:3": "A mendicant cannot rest confident ",
    "dhp272:4": "without attaining the end of defilements. ",
    "dhp272:5": ""
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "dhp256:2": "sāhasā → sahasā (bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp260:1": "thero so hoti → thero hoti (bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp261:4": "thero” iti → so theroti (sya-all, mr); thero ti (pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp267:2": "brahmacariyavā → brahmacariyaṁ (mr) "
  },
